Aetiology of the cosmic safehold

    : re `cosmic safehold` see ../ : The presence throughout the cosmos
      of a safehold fit for securing our long-term survival
    - there is no obvious cause for its presence
        - here I will look into it, surveying the potential causes for its presence
        - my [specific] aim here is to define a set ‚Å†X‚Å† of potential causal explanantia ‚Å†x_1,x_2,x_3,\dots‚Å†
          for the explanandum ‚Å†y‚Å†, given as follows

            ‚Å†\boldsymbol{y}‚Å† : The fitness of the cosmos (for use) as a safehold for securing our long-term survival.

    - now already cosmology has looked into a phenomenon of similar scope and pertinence, namely
      the fine tuning of the cosmos for life, and sought the potential causes for *its* presence
        - thus we have predefined [for us] a set ‚Å†X'‚Å† of potential causal explanantia
          for an explanandum that is comparable to ‚Å†y‚Å†, namely that of:

            ‚Å†\boldsymbol{y'}‚Å† : The fine tuning of the physical laws, constants and conditions of the cosmos for life.

        ‚à¥ one may begin by using the predefined set ‚Å†X'‚Å† to define the initial members of ‚Å†X‚Å†, as follows

            for( each potential causal explanans ‚Å†x_i‚Å† of set ‚Å†X'‚Å† ) where ‚Å†i=1,2,3,\dots‚Å†
                ‚ÅÉ divorce ‚Å†x_i‚Å† from explanandum ‚Å†y'‚Å†
                    : note : that is all for ‚Å†y'‚Å†, fine tuning will not be a premise
                      of the present aetiology
                ‚ÅÉ reapply ‚Å†x_i‚Å† instead, mutatis mutandis, to explanandum ‚Å†y‚Å†
                ‚ÅÉ add the resulting ‚Å†x_i‚Å† to set ‚Å†X‚Å†

        - what follows is [based on] the result
    ‚îÄ initial potential causes and their premises:
        necessity
            : privately see `^*‚Ä¢ .*${same}$` @ `from the field of fine tuning$` @
              ._/01.tale-of-logic_form/._/40.a_search_for_explanations.notes.brec
            : see also `^^multiverse ensemble \+.${same}$`i
        design
            : privately see `^*‚Ä¢ .*${same}$` @ `from the field of fine tuning$` @
              ._/01.tale-of-logic_form/._/40.a_search_for_explanations.notes.brec
            : see                 `^^God \+.${same}$`i
            : see `^^multiverse ensemble \+.${same}$`i
        God +¬†design
        multiverse ensemble
            : privately see `^*‚Ä¢ .*${same}$` @ `from the field of fine tuning$` @
              ._/01.tale-of-logic_form/._/40.a_search_for_explanations.notes.brec
            : see `^^${same} \+.necessity$`i
            : see `^^${same} \+.design$`i
    ‚îÄ further potential causes and their premises:
        multiverse ensemble +¬†necessity
            : re `necessity` see also
            : privately note : here the principal added premise is a necessarily tight coupling between
              a cosmos‚Äôs habitability and safeholding capacity, the universal structure of reality being
              such that the set of cosmic properties necessary for the former will in most cases (in most
              combinations of their permitted values) happen also to suffice for the latter
                : cf. `^*-.+the claim: hardly could life exist absent a speed limit on causation$`
                  @ ._/01.tale-of-logic_form/._/60.vetting_their_explanantia.notes.brec
        multiverse ensemble +¬†design
